Error: Error: "Unable To Allocate More Memory: Increase -Xmx Argument"



Step-By-Step

Solution: 1. Log in to your Pterodactyl Panel.
2. Click on the "Console" option for the server.
3. Stop the server by typing "/stop" into the console and then hitting enter.
4. Click on the "Startup Parameters" option and scroll down to find the "-Xmx" option.
